T|09 ·|0|The date-based view of the long-form cn machine — when each vd is scripted, filmed, edited, and published, so cadence is visible at a glance.
T|09 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|A calendar layout over the cn Pipeline so the owner can see cn scheduled across days/weeks and confirm the publishing cadence (e.g. 1 vd/week) is being met. It is the "Calendar" counterpart to the cn Pipeline's Kanban.
T|Purp|1|
X|What|0|A weekly/monthly grid w/ cn cards placed on their target dates (filming days, edit days, publish dates).
X|What|1|Each entry tied to a cn Pipeline card and its stage (Scripting → Filming → Editing → Ready → Published).
X|What|2|Cadence/health at a glance: gaps in the schedule are visible, so the owner can keep the funnel full.
X|What|3|
T|Rela|0|Shares data w/ cn Pipeline (08) — same cards, different (date) view, reachable via that page's Calendar toggle.
T|Rela|1|Distinct from Scheduler (15), which schedules sl posts across platforms; the Production Calendar is abt long-form vd production.
T|Rela|2|
T|Rela|3|Confidence: Listed in the sidebar (LONG-FORM section) and referenced via the cn Pipeline's "Calendar" view, but not shown as a dedicated full screen in the captured screenshots. Layout above is inferred from its name and role.